<HEAD>Woman Arrested For Fleeing Marine Patrol On Sailboard</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STUART, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A 54-year-old windsurfer was arrested and booked into jail in a wet bathing suit after she allegedly tried to use her board to make a getaway from a <ORGANIZATION> Florida </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Marine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Patrol </ORGANIZATION> officer. <PERSON> Jean </PERSON> <PERSON> Felicia </PERSON> <PERSON> Kuznar </PERSON>, of <LOCATION> Jensen </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Beach </LOCATION>, was charged with careless operation of a vessel, interfering with navigation, resisting arrest without violence, and fleeing and eluding law officers. Her problems with Officer <PERSON> Leslie </PERSON> <PERSON> Jones </PERSON> began when Mrs. <PERSON> Kuznar </PERSON> was windsurfing Wednesday near the <PERSON> Stuart </PERSON> <PERSON> Causeway </PERSON> and a powerboat entered the channel. Ms. <PERSON> Jones </PERSON> said the powerboat had to `` take evasive action to avoid an accident,'' so she approached Mrs. <PERSON> Kuznar </PERSON> in her patrol boat to discuss the matter. Ms. <PERSON> Jones </PERSON> said Mrs. <PERSON> Kuznar </PERSON> refused orders that she bring her windsurfer to shore and `` told me to get lost.'' Mrs. <PERSON> Kuznar </PERSON> said she was trying to get to shore, and complained that the officer swamped her with the patrol boat's wake.
