<FIRST>u p AM-ConventionOverview Bjt   07-23 0818</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Convention Overview, Bjt,850</SECOND>
<HEAD>What Began With A Question Mark Ended With An Exclamation Point</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOHN KING</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Democrats, who began their quadrennial convention with the threat of discord, headed home in dramatic unity to fight the fall battle for the White House. `` This has been a great convention and it sets the stage for a great Democratic win in November,'' the star attraction, <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>, told weary delegates gathered for one last party early Friday. His nomination was a given coming into <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION>, but the atmosphere in which he would accept it was uncertain. <PERSON> Jesse </PERSON> <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON>'s bus caravan rolled in Saturday with the runner-up in the primaries unsure whether he `` had a place at the table.'' <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> arrived Sunday but refused to meet with the edgy <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> until he sat down with his trusted advisers to assess preliminary talks between the two camps. Republicans had a `` truth squad'' in town and took advantage of the apparent rift to boast of divided Democrats and a nominee-to-be powerless to control his convention. But a show of unity just hours before <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> Kirk </PERSON> gaveled the party's 40th convention to order on Monday night ended most talk of discord, although Republicans continued to assert <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> was stealing the show. After a nearly three-hour meeting Monday, <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> and <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> declared their differences resolved, with <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> promising <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> a role in the fall campaign and <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> in turn promising his support. `` We did not come here for fireworks; we came here for noble works,'' <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> said. With that, the convention opened _ to verbal fireworks, all aimed at the Republicans. Keynote speaker <PERSON> Ann </PERSON> <PERSON> Richards </PERSON> pumped up the more than 4,000 delegates with fiery rhetoric that lampooned <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>'s claim of <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> as his home state and portrayed the vice president as a do-nothing member of a disgraced administration. `` I want to announce to the nation that in a little more than 100 days the Reagan-Meese-Deaver-Nofziger-Poindexter-North-Weinberger-Watt-Gorsuch-Lavelle-Stockman-Haig-Bork-Noriega-George <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> era will be over,'' the <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> treasurer said to thunderous applause. The redeemed <PERSON> Jimmy </PERSON> <PERSON> Carter </PERSON> made a prime-time appearance, too, adding his call for moral government to a convention with a deliberate Southern flavor. <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> had his night Tuesday, declaring himself qualified for the presidency and predicting he would occupy the White House in the future while urging his backers to support <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> in the fall. In a show of respect, many <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> delegates gave up their hall passes to <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> alternates and supporters and <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> placards were kept low while a sea of red proclaimed `` <PERSON> Jesse </PERSON>!'' Despite that gesture, not all of <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON>'s backers got into the Omni convention hall. Thousands were kept out after <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION>'s fire marshal decided too many people had already been let in, a problem that continued throughout the four-day gathering. Monday's detente had removed the potential for acrimony Wednesday, when <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> won the party's blessing to take on <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>. All that was left was to crown the nominee, and after the rousing speeches of <PERSON> Richards </PERSON> and <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON>, there was some worry the star of the show might be upstaged. But actress cousin <PERSON> Olympia </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>, in a supporting role once again, warmed the audience with an introduction of <PERSON> 