<HEAD>Monsoon Toll Rises to 255</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Rains and landslides were reported across <LOCATION> India </LOCATION> on Saturday, and the death toll from the annual monsoon rains rose to 255, reports said. The hill resort of Simla in the northern state of <LOCATION> Himachal </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Pradesh </LOCATION> was cut off for the third day, the <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trust </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> India </ORGANIZATION> reported. Rail and road traffic to <LOCATION> Simla </LOCATION>, the state capital, has been disrupted because of landslides and heavy rains. At least 20 more deaths were reported as a result of the rain, which began last month. The rain, eagerly awaited by Indians after three years of drought, has caused widespread flooding. In <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Delhi </LOCATION>, officials began evacuating people living in low-lying areas near the <LOCATION> Yamuna </LOCATION> river. Warnings were issued to villagers living on the outskirts of the capital because of the rising water levels of the river, the <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trust </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> India </ORGANIZATION> said. Five people died in <LOCATION> Himachal </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Pradesh </LOCATION> state in floods or landslides, the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> India </ORGANIZATION> reported. Eight more people were killed when heavy rains caused a mudslide in northeastern <LOCATION> Bombay </LOCATION>, the news agency said. Three people died in <LOCATION> Jammu </LOCATION> district in <LOCATION> Kashmir </LOCATION> state when their hut collapsed, and four people died in <LOCATION> Uttar </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Pradesh </LOCATION> state, <ORGANIZATION> UNI </ORGANIZATION> said. Most of the deaths occurred in the past 24 hours.
