<HEAD>Reagan Proclaims Lyme Disease Awareness Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTA BARBARA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> on Saturday proclaimed the week of July 24-30 as Lyme Disease Awareness Week. <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> said in a statement that Lyme Disease afflicts `` a growing number of Americans each year'' and has been identified in more than 30 states. Lyme Disease, first identified by scientists in 1975, is spread by the bite of a tiny deer tick. `` The best treatment for Lyme Disease is prevention,'' <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON>'s proclamation said `` People must know the dangers associated with ticks and take necessary precautions when hiking. They should check regularly for the presence of ticks, know how to remove them and be alert for symptoms of Lyme Disease.''
