o withdraw its troops but the rebels, who did not sign the agreement, vowed to fight on. <PERSON> Zia </PERSON> denied <LOCATION> Pakistan </LOCATION> has violated the <LOCATION> Geneva </LOCATION> accords. The Afghan government has lodged almost 55 complaints with a U.N monitoring team, accusing <LOCATION> Pakistan </LOCATION> of harboring guerrillas, supplying them with weapons and allowing a resistance government to establish itself on Pakistani soil.
