<TEXT>
 Here are some commodity price trends for the past week. Grain and soybean futures retreated on the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trade </ORGANIZATION>. Wheat for delivery in September settled Friday at $ 3.84 -LCB- a bushel compared with $ 3.93 -LCB- a week earlier; September corn fell to $ 3.12 -LCB- a bushel from $ 3.43; September oats skidded to $ 2.60 a bushel from $ 3.17 -LCB-; and August soybeans plunged to $ 8.30 -LCB- a bushel from $ 9.91 -LCB-. Livestock and meat futures rose on the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. August live cattle advanced to 66.12 cents a pound from 64.27 cents; August feeder cattle rose to 77.37 cents a pound from 74.75 cents; August hogs finished at 46.12 cents a pound compared with 44.37 cents; and July frozen pork bellies expired Friday at 39.75 cents a pound compared with 37.30 cents a week earlier. Precious metals moved higher on <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Commodity </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. August gold advanced to $ 442.90 a troy ounce from $ 441.30; July silver moved to $ 7.606 a troy ounce from $ 7.310. Energy futures leaped higher on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. West Texas Intermediate crude oil for September delivery settled at $ 16.38 a barrel, up from $ 14.97; August heating oil surged to 44.95 cents a gallon from 41.12 cents; unleaded gasoline improved to 52.07 cents a gallon from 49.73 cents.
